<kml>

<concept name=Conceal>
<superconcept name=Make-Inaccessible>

<hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Conceal>
  <definition>Cause an object to be physically or visibly hidden (possibly to another object)</definition>
  <requiredslot name=object>
    <restriction>a Tangible-Entity</restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <primaryslot name=agent>
    <restriction>causes <slot>object</slot> to be Concealed</restriction>
  </primaryslot>
  <primaryslot name=base>
    <comment>the Entity that the <slot>object</slot> is Concealed from</comment>
  </primaryslot>
  <wnsynsets><verb>conceal#1
  </verb></wnsynsets>
  <wnsynsets><verb>hide#1
  </verb></wnsynsets>
</component>

<musing>
Conceal puts an <slot>object</slot> in a <conceptref name=Be-Concealed> 
state, which can be undone by <conceptref name=Expose>.
</musing>

</kml>


